Rural revitalization, talent is the key.
Where to find talent?
The excellent group of returning migrant workers is an indispensable force.
Xinhua News Agency sent Shang Hai Chun works
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26th topic: To make excellent returning migrant workers into a rural revitalization force
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing, where he paid tens of thousands of dollars a month, and returned to his hometown to start a business.
After several years of hard work, now he runs the wine-growing family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, became a famous leader of the rich, and was selected to enter the village“two committees”team.
In recent years, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometown to start a business, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside, inspired by a series of policies to support farmers and benefit farmers, such as the country's efforts to eradicate poverty and revitalize the countryside.
In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village Party branch secretaries, 61,000 village reserve forces and more than 20,000 party members were generated from the outstanding migrant workers returned, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Well-off is not well-off, the key to look at fellow countrymen.
Since the reform and opening-up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural China have gone out to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
But objectively, it has also led to the emergence of“hollow”in rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations, and the“one old and one low”characteristics of the village party branch secretaries and party members, namely the aging of age, low education, and the problem of the lack of leadership in the village party organizations.
If the rural talent and other elements have been one-way flow to the city, the countryside for a long time in the state of“blood loss” and “anemia”, revitalization is an empty word.
Attracting those migrant workers who have the ability, awareness and ambition to serve their hometown, guiding them to return to their hometown to start their own businesses and become leaders in getting rich, training them to become party members and rural cadres on a merit-based basis, and enriching the cadres at the grass-roots level is the strategy to solve the problem of the disparity between the ranks of rural party members and the grass-roots party organizations.
Good migrant workers will be brought back, but also let them stay and do well.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict candidate criteria, it has established a system and mechanism for the targeted return of outstanding migrant workers, service guarantee, training and selection, so that they can improve their ability, guarantee their work and hope in their lives, so that they can truly take root in the countryside and have a sense of accomplishment in starting their own businesses.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty. Talent is the key factor to do a good job of bridging poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers. Through comprehensive measures, they will be built into a team and force that can stay, fight and take away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and personnel support for the rural areas to get rid of poverty and achieve a well-off and revitalization of development.
