The natural ecology of the capital continues to attract wildlife to the city " to settle”
More than 500 species of wild animals have been found in Beijing
Newspaper news (reporter Wang Bin) Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the city landscaping Bureau, in recent years, with the capital's natural ecological environment continues to improve, the species and number of wild animals will continue to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife living in Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including brown horse chicken, black stork and other state-level protected animals, as well as gazelle, swan, crane, mandarin duck and other state-level protected animals.
Whether it is planted into a city forest in the second ring road, or embedded in the small and micro-wetland between buildings, not only for the urban people to bring nature's wild interest, but also attract wild animals to the city to“settle”.
In midsummer, Songshan National Nature Reserve, located in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District, is flourishing.
A raccoon is playing leisurely by the mountain stream,while two wolverines fight with each other.
Looking back, a wild boar could not resist the body of the "prick", is rubbing hard against the bark.Hu Qiaoli, director of the Management Department of Songshan National Nature Reserve, said that as of the end of 2019, in the green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, there are 178 species of wild animals, including the golden eagle of the state-level protected animals and the spoon chicken and the gazelle of the state-level protected animals.
"In Matsuyama, wild animals are the real' masters‘, and our staff can at best be regarded as people's’bodyguards'.”
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the wildlife in the protected area, more than 30 professional rangers are patrolling along 16 well-established protection routes every day. Every month, there will be a“big circle”, spending a full day traveling almost the entire protected area.
"During the inspection, it is necessary not only to check the record of biodiversity, but also to check the installation of artificial nests, rescue injured wildlife, installation of field infrared cameras and so on.”
More than 200 infrared cameras have been installed in Songshan National Nature Reserve to record the living status of wild animals in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli said that with the abundance of biodiversity in protected areas in recent years, more and more wild animals appear in the camera, ocelot, raccoon and pig badger has become the“resident guest”, the“appearance rate”of the national second-level protected animal gazelle is also getting higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, Director of the Department of Wildlife, Flora and Fauna and Wetland Protection of the Beijing Bureau of Landscaping, said that the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife in Beijing has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 species today, and the number of wildlife species and numbers in Beijing has continued to increase in recent years.
The presence of wild animals in the city is more and more common, closely related to the upgrading of greening in the capital city in recent years.
In particular, the new round of afforestation and greening construction started in 2018 proposed to reshape the urban ecological environment,enhance the ecological function of woodland green space, and highlight the concept of“near nature”.
Planning to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green areas, to facilitate wildlife "visiting friends and relatives", the trees are also animals love honey source, food source plants.
