Shenzhen seeks public opinion on health regulations-Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (reporter Mao Siqian, Bai Yu) Encourage residents to do physical examination, early detection of problems;prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish an online game health censorship system; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel...... Recently, the“Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (draft for solicitation of comments)”officially released, Shenzhen residents will have their own " health law."
In order to encourage residents to carry out regular medical examinations and detect problems at an early stage, the above draft proposes that the health and health departments should formulate a basic catalogue of health check-up items according to different factors such as age and occupation.
The expenses for health examination that fall within the scope of the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the social medical insurance co-ordination Fund in accordance with the standard once a year for each person.
The draft for Solicitation of Comments makes it clear that the employing unit shall rationally allocate human resources, arrange the work schedule of employees, implement a system of rest for employees with heavy mental and physical labor loads, so as to avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health harm to the health of employees, and strictly implement the system of paid leave for employees.
In addition, employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize and carry out employee health check-ups.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the draft proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, while restrictions are imposed on the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages, and those who violate the provisions will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections and fined 30,000 yuan.
In addition to“prohibition”, minors also have to“exercise more. ”
In accordance with the requirements of the draft, the school should arrange more than one hour of physical activity for students every day.
With regard to online games, public security, culture, radio, television, tourism, sports, internet supervision, health and health departments should improve the system of health supervision in Internet service business premises, establish a system of health censorship for online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposes that influenza patients must wear masks in public places, medical and health institutions without consent to disclose patient privacy fines of 20,000 yuan.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires Shenzhen departments to assess the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating planning and normative documents involving urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource exploitation and ecological environmental protection, and the development of the biomedical industry, as well as before approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
Where no assessment has been made or the assessment will have a more serious adverse effect on the public health of the city or on the health of the residents, it shall not be formulated, promulgated or approved for implementation.
