Kekexili Tibetan antelope enters the migration season-Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, July 25 (Reporter Wang Jinjin) Reporters learned from the Sanjiangyuan National Park Director Jiangyuan Park Kekexili Management Office Wudaoliang protection station, monitoring shows that the tibetan antelope that had previously gone to the Zhonai Lake area in the hinterland of Kekexili are ending litter, began to return with their cubs to their original habitat.
Surveillance footage near the Wudaoliang Protection Station showed that on July 25, about 40 female antelope led three antelope cubs through the Wudaoliang North Bridge of the Qinghai-Tibet Railway, 3002 kilometers from the Qinghai-Tibet Highway, and the antelope had begun to move back.
In recent years, the number of pups of the Tibetan antelope has accounted for one-fourth to one-fifth of the total population of the Tibetan antelope herd, experts said.
Lian Xinming, associate researcher at the Northwest Institute of Plateau Biology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, said:“In the early stages of migration, Tibetan antelope faces a higher risk of being eaten, so the number of pups in the flock will be relatively small, and even there may be no pups.”
According to the statistics of the Kekexili Administration Office of Jiangyuan Park, Director of the Sanjiangyuan National Park, the number of Tibetan antelope relocation has increased year by year. In 2019, the number of Tibetan antelope relocation was 4,860, an increase of 338 compared with 2018.
Lian Xinming said: "It is expected that this year the return of the tibetan antelope will end in early September,the number of the return of the tibetan antelope is still expected to continue to increase.”
The Tibetan antelope is a protected animal at the national level.
At the end of May every year, Tibetan antelope from Qinghai Sanjiangyuan, Tibet Qiangtang, Xinjiang Aljinshan and other places go to Zhuonai Lake in the hinterland of Kekexili to lay lambs.
Wu Xiaomin, an expert on the protection of tibetan antelope and a researcher at the Shaanxi Institute of Zoology (Northwest Institute of Endangered Animals) in China, said:“The return of the tibetan antelope is the process of the female antelope returning to its habitat after the end of the litter.At first, the population of the antelope is larger, but then the antelope will return to their habitat along different paths according to different geographical populations.”
In order to ensure the safe relocation of the Tibetan antelope herd, the reporter learned that recently Sanjiangyuan National Park management director Jiangyuan Park Kekexili management office has arranged staff in the main relocation area, continue to carry out video monitoring and area patrol.
If a herd of tibetan antelope is found trying to cross the road, the mountain patrol team will conduct temporary traffic control at the first time, so that the flock can safely pass through the wildlife channel, to ensure that they are on the way back to the least possible human interference.
So, in the end, how to relieve the heat in daily life?
Experts recommend that summer go out as far as possible to avoid the heat period, it is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon, because this time the sun is the strongest, the possibility of heat stroke is higher.
If you must go out at this time, be sure to do a good job of protection, such as umbrellas, sunshades, sunglasses, the best conditions to apply sunscreen to prevent sunburn.
Clothes try to choose light color, good breathability of cotton, hemp, silk texture, wear less chemical fiber category clothing, so as not to heat up in time when a lot of sweating, causing heat stroke.
When hot and sultry weather, to prepare enough water to drink, drink in time, do not wait for thirst before drinking water, because once you feel thirsty indicates that the body has a shortage of water, each drink water control in 150 ml to 200 ml, drink warm water, do not drink ice water.
According to the temperature level, the average staff drink 1.5 liters to 2 liters of water a day, high temperature workers, drink 3 liters to 5 liters of water a day.
Sweating more can be appropriate to add some salt water, make up for the body lost due to sweating salt.
