A small plane crashed in the Swiss Alps, killing all four people on board-<url>
Beijing, July 26, according to the European Network, citing the European Unicom news agency, local time on July 25, the Swiss police told the media that a small plane crashed in the Swiss Alps on the 25th.
All two Swiss and two Austrians on board were killed in the accident.
A small plane crashed more than 3,000 metres above sea level near the alpine peaks of the canton of Valais, and rescuers rushed to the scene of the crash to confirm that all four people aboard were killed, according to a police statement in the southern Swiss canton of Wallis.
Valais Police said a witness called the police at 12: 25 p.m. on the 25th to report that he had witnessed a small plane falling from the sky.
A few minutes later, witnesses reported to the police again that smoke was billowing from the crash site.
After receiving the alarm, the police quickly coordinated fire police, medical staff and rescue personnel and carried a helicopter to the scene of the accident to rescue.
