China's Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020 (hereinafter referred to as the "Report"), released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, shows that by the impact of the epidemic, the first five months of 2020, China's shared accommodation market transaction volume decreased by 72.1% year-on-year.
However, the shared accommodation market has been picking up since March, with a gradual recovery in turnover, orders and reception.
"The report" shows that the share accommodation market transaction volume fell sharply, on the one hand due to the epidemic prevention and control of travel accommodation demand fell sharply, the volume of orders fell sharply, the first five months of total orders fell 65% year-on-year, reception people fell 63% year-on-year; on the other hand, the weakness of demand also led to a more significant decline in night prices, the first five months of average night prices fell 16% year-on-year.
