According to the survey and design party of China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd. Zhengwan high-speed rail tunnel design director Wangjun, the location of the small three-gap tunnel is very complex terrain geological conditions, facing karst, mud surges, soft rock deformation and other risks, is a class i high-risk tunnel, tunnel design and construction is extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical exploration method and advanced drilling method to advance geological forecasting, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 types of caves.Such as the design and construction of a 24-meter long bridge, across the tunnel in the longitudinal length of more than 10 meters, depth of more than 55 meters of large caves, to avoid tunnel settlement."Said the Royal Army.
According to the construction party China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction of the tunnel, through the construction of horizontal guidance, grouting water blocking, strengthening the tunnel structure support and the construction of sewage treatment station, not only to ensure the orderly progress of the project, but also to avoid the construction of drainage damage to the small three Gorges scenic area water bodies, at the same time successfully overcome the 7 km long soft rock large deformation and other bad geology, the daily maximum amount of water up to 157,000 cubic meters of multi-burst mud gush water and other construction problems.
When the full line of the Zhengwan High-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new main convenient and fast passenger route to the central plains, North China and Northeast China in southwest China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast-to-southwest railway route, improve the layout of the regional road network, speed up the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote regional coordinated development and promote the implementation of the strategy for the development of the Western region.
