The overall stability of employment and prices highlights the“temperature " of the economy”
Lin Huocan, Reporter of China Economic Network, Economic Daily News and China Economic Network
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China has taken overall measures to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The situation of epidemic prevention and control has continued to improve, the steady economic recovery has been obvious, and the performance of employment and prices, which are closely related to the people's livelihood, has been generally stable.
The unemployment rate rose in the first two months of the year.
In February, in particular, many enterprises ' production and operation activities were largely shut down,with reduced demand for workers, delays or cancellations of hiring, and rising unemployment rates in urban surveys.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the order of production and life of the whole society has been restored continuously.
The Central Committee of the Party will adhere to the overall tone of steady progress, further increase macro-policy hedging, strengthen the employment priority policy in an all-round way, and actively promote the work of helping to stabilize and expand employment.
China has increased its policies to hedge stable positions,played a combination of”relief and relief and compensation " policies.Three social insurance units have been exempted from payment of social insurance contributions in a phased manner, allowing the postponement of payment of social insurance contributions, expanding the return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized and micro-enterprises, and benefiting from the policy of working on behalf of training, and giving absorption subsidies and apprenticeship subsidies to enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of the steady employment policies, the demand for employment in enterprises has picked up steadily, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the unemployment rate in urban surveys has gradually declined, with the unemployment rate in June at 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Department of Population and Employment Statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to bear fruit, the labor force withdrawn due to the impact of the epidemic in the early period has returned, the urban labor participation rate in June compared with February rose by about 10 percentage points, close to the level of the same period last year.
The data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached pre-epidemic levels.The average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, an increase of 6.6 hours over February and a slightly higher 0.1 hours than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January, the CPI rose 5.4 per cent year-on-year, a year-on-year high.
Entering February, the year-on-year increase in CPI, although slightly down, is still in the“5 range”.
CPI year-on-year growth is at a high level, both before the Spring Festival consumer demand pull factors, but also the Spring Festival wrong month and a lower year-on-year base factors.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the epidemic prevention and control, in January and February, there were logistics delays, lack of timely supply of materials, increased material transport costs and other conditions, coupled with some citizens hoarding and snapping up, the price of some necessities of life increased significantly.
In order to cope with the disturbance caused by the epidemic epidemic prevention and control on the price situation, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Under the action of a series of policy initiatives, the market supply of vegetables and fruits has been effectively guaranteed.
In order to cope with the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the Central Government introduced a policy of ensuring and stabilizing prices, the rapid implementation of the policy in all regions and departments, the supply of pork reserves has improved significantly, the production capacity of pigs has been restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and marketing has gradually been normal.
In March, pork prices fell continuously,and food prices rose to 10.6% year-on-year in May.In June, pork prices rose slightly sequentially due to factors such as slowing pig exports, reduced imports and a rebound in group consumer demand.
Seasonal changes in the price of fresh vegetables were marked, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half.
Affected by the higher base of comparison in the same period last year, fresh fruit prices continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half.
The basic life of the masses is effectively guaranteed,and the overall economic and social situation remains stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of traffic and logistics, local increased supply and supply efforts,the market supply and demand situation improved.
Starting in March, the CPI fell for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase fell from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, with prices generally returning to a steady state.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level,the overall inflationary pressure is not small, but still under the premise of doing a good job in the prevention and control of the epidemic situation, promote the restoration of production and life order.
Effectively deal with natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main producing areas of grain, fruits and vegetables and other agricultural products, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on hoarding and driving up prices and other acts that disrupt market order.
