Is it reasonable for a 3-year-old child to sue the school after being hit by a play on the college playground?
2020-07-26 05:01: 11 Source: Legal Daily Author: Wang Sishuo Responsible editor: Wang Sishuo
The playground was smashed,and the children were compensated and then sued the school
□ Newspaper correspondent Zhao Yifan
Xiaowen, 3, was accidentally hit in the head by Chen from the softball team while playing on a college playground.
After Chen's compensation, Xiaowen's father, Mr. Wen, as Xiaowen's legal representative, sued the school to the court, demanding that the school where the playground was located apologize, and pay a total of 20,000 yuan for medical expenses and psychological damage.
Recently, after hearing the case, the People's Court of Haidian District of Beijing held that the school had set up a protective net in the playground at the time of the incident and had fulfilled the appropriate safety and security obligations, and Chen had made compensation, and accordingly the judgment rejected the plaintiff's claim.
Mr. Wen claims that during the summer vacation of 2019, he took Xiaowen to play on the school playground while the softball team was training on the playground.
In order to avoid the risks, Siu Man, Mr. Man and many other children and parents are active in the safe areas designated by the softball team.
But then the softball team member Chen dropped the ball while pitching, causing the softball over the net to fly to the safety area and hit Xiaowen in the back of the head.
Mr. Wen immediately took Xiaowen to the hospital for treatment and was diagnosed with head trauma.
Mr. Man believes that the facilities of the school's stadium do not comply with the relevant safety regulations and do not manage the team and related facilities effectively.
The school's negligence led to the above-mentioned events, resulting in the small tattoo body suffered great pain,but also brought greater pain to his family, for which the school should bear legal responsibility.
In this regard, the school argued that the school has set up a protective net in the playground, and posted management regulations, training notice, telling to enter the playground must maintain a safe distance from the training site and remind attention to their own safety, the plaintiff can not prove that the school“failed to meet the obligations of safety and security”, so do not agree to compensation.
The court heard that the venue of the incident was a free venue open to the public by the university involved. Although the school has a safety and security obligation for the management of the playground, this safety and security obligation only needs to meet the general obligation to pay attention.
At the time of the incident, the school had set up a protective net in the playground, which had fulfilled the appropriate security obligations, and Chen also compensated Xiaowen for medical expenses, transportation expenses and other losses of more than 2,000 yuan in accordance with the compensation agreement reached earlier.
After that, Xiaowen's parents again claimed the school's compensation,and the court ruled that all the plaintiff's claims were dismissed.
After the verdict, neither party appealed,and the verdict is now in force.
According to Article 37 of the Tort Liability Law of our country, the school, as the administrator of public places, has the obligation of safety and security; in the case of damage caused by the actions of a third person, the third person shall bear the tort liability, but the administrator of public places who have not fulfilled the obligation of safety and security shall bear the corresponding supplementary responsibility.
According to the judge, as the administrator of a public place, he is most likely to understand the actual situation of the whole place, foresee the risks and damage that may occur, and thus is most likely to take the necessary measures to prevent the occurrence of loss or to mitigate the extent of the damage, and the cost of avoiding and mitigating the occurrence of the damage is minimal, so the law stipulates that he shall bear the corresponding safeguard obligation to engage in social activities.
In this case, the school's duty of safety and security should be commensurate with the social activities it engages in in the playground, which is open to the public free of charge. In particular, it should mainly take basic security measures and have the obligation to inform about hidden dangers.
In judicial practice, it is also not appropriate to impose excessive safety and security obligations on public place managers.
If the school has taken to set up a protective network and fulfill the obligation to inform, it can be found that the school is not at fault and should not bear legal responsibility.
In addition, even if the administrators of schools and other public places fail to fulfill their obligations of safety and security, their liability is also supplemented by compensation for damages. In accordance with the newly promulgated civil code, the administrators may also recover compensation from the third party after assuming the additional responsibility.
Therefore, in such an accident, the victim shall not extend the scope of the claim after he has received compensation from the direct infringer.
Today I want to show you how we will make things in the future.
