Beijing News(Reporter Liu Zhen)On July 26, the Beijing Philharmonic Choir published an obituary. Yang Hongnian, the founder of the Beijing Philharmonic Choir, a famous Chinese conductor and music educator, a tenured academic member of the Central Conservatory of Music and a professor of the Conducting Department, died on July 26, 2020 at 13: 55 in Beijing, at the age of 86, due to ineffective medical treatment.
Photo from the official website of the Beijing Philharmonic Choir.
Yang Hongnian was born in 1934, a native of Nanjing, Jiangsu Province, and loved music from an early age.
