In 1958, he taught at the Music Department of the Beijing Normal University of the Arts, and in 1973 he was transferred to the Composition Department and the Conductor Department of the Central Conservatory of Music.
Yang Hongnian founded the Beijing Philharmonic Choir in 1983.
For more than 30 years, he has led the choir around the world with the aim of“love and dedication”and won dozens of awards in important competitions at home and abroad.
He has conducted the performances of more than 30 groups such as the Central Orchestra Chorus, the Central National Song and Dance Troupe, the Oriental Song and Dance Troupe and the Shanghai Choir, and held a number of symphonic concerts and choral concerts.
