The Lancet article commends China's anti-epidemic efforts and encourages countries to learn from their experiences-<url>
As a country with a population of 1.4 billion and a size similar to Europe or the United States, China has effectively controlled the new crown epidemic at this stage, without the widespread spread, and has largely controlled the domestic epidemic, the Lancet magazine said on the 25th.
China has invested heavily in domestic research and public health over the past decade, making it much more prepared for the new crown than it was for severe acute respiratory syndrome(SARS), the article said.
At the time of the SARS outbreak in 2002, China was initially unprepared, especially when the pathogen could not be identified, the authors said.
When the new crown virus was discovered in December 2019, Chinese scientists were quickly able to identify the virus species and shared genome sequencing data with the international community on January 11, 2020.
By the end of January, doctors from mainland China and Hong Kong had clarified the clinical features of the virus, warning the world of the threat of the new crown virus through a research paper published in the Lancet.
China has also been at the forefront of vaccine research, which has been carried out very quickly and rigorously through close domestic cooperation under a state of emergency, and in May and July, the Lancet published the results of early trials of the new crown vaccine developed by China, respectively.
China's experience shows that it is very important to invest in the national health and research system to effectively improve laboratory capacity.
This is the basis for a rapid and effective national response to health emergencies and global health security.
Other countries, especially low-and middle-income countries, are well worth learning from and learning from.
In addition, China's experience has proved that on the basis of strong research, there must be a strong high-level decisively and scientifically based to make the right decision, which can make the new crown epidemic is effectively controlled.
The article emphasizes that governments and their leaders must respect science, understand the value of science and act on it in the most beneficial way to society.
In the early stages of the outbreak, China's State Health and Construction Ministry sent three groups of infectious disease experts to Wuhan to investigate the risk and spread of the new crown virus. Their recommendations provided the basis for the decision to“seal the city”of Wuhan on January 23.
At the end of the article, it is emphasized that countries need to strengthen global cooperation and joint response to global health emergencies.
