I want to create an online air quality management platform that will reveal future pollution trends and make predictions about what might happen.
I am sure that my idea can become a realistic solution, but also faced with uncertainty, I can not guarantee that it will succeed.
All I have is a specific set of engineer skills, the skills I have gained from my work. (Laughter) Of course, for someone who has been working in the field of air pollution for years, my skills are completely new.
I've come to realize that sometimes a novel perspective, a new skill set, can lead to something remarkable.
Our willpower and imagination are an indicator of how we move past obstacles and start a new chapter.
I had a better understanding of air pollution, looking for air pollution data over the past ten years, as well as meteorological data in and around Johannesburg. After that, I worked with my colleagues in South Africa and China to create an air quality resolution support system and upload it to the cloud.
