Before you volunteer, figure out what a professional difference is.
Every year, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the volunteer application, and thus affect the volunteer application.
This year, Beijing Jiaotong University,Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, Beijing University of Chemical Technology, five universities jointly issued the 2020 enrollment policy, eliminating the professional grade difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference,and what is the significance of voluntary filing?
There are three ways of professional assignment rules
Experts remind, before filling in the volunteer, be sure to read the "admissions charter" of your favorite school, understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the ratio of adjustment, professional allocation rules and so on.
Professional allocation rules, refers to the college after the shift, for the major admission there are three major priority, score priority, professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be clear in the "Admissions Charter".
But there are also some colleges and universities admission principle is the overall score priority,there is no difference between the major.
When the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score line, then see whether to reach the second professional volunteer admission score line, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called”professional grade difference“is when colleges and universities arrange candidates for majors, according to one or more of the score values published in the admissions regulations, to determine the admission of candidates for different professional voluntary candidates, this score value is”professional grade difference".
That is, the difference between the scores of the institutions in the admission of candidates in the first professional volunteer and non-first professional volunteer, the difference between the professional volunteer scores, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point and so on.
For example.
Suppose the student Xiaoming reported A university, the test of 560 points, their professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering,e-commerce, A university's professional admission practice professional grade difference method, the difference is divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, 0 points.
If the computer is not accepted, then his score will be subtracted by 2 points, according to the score of 558 points and the first professional volunteer to apply for“international trade”candidates, to determine whether the professional admission requirements are met; if still not met, the score is subtracted by 1 point(i.e. 557 points)for the third professional volunteer“automated”admission; if still not met, the score is subtracted by 1 point(i.e. 556 points)for the fourth professional volunteer“automated”admission If the subsequent major is still unable to meet its professional volunteers, it will no longer reduce the points, and so on.
Different university professional grade difference settings are different
With the popularity of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have canceled the professional grade difference, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year, from the "admissions charter" published by the schools, this year there are mainly more than 20 universities set the professional grade difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University,Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight College, etc.
In these colleges and universities, each university set a different professional grade difference.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates who have been submitted to the university in the file are admitted according to the order in which candidates fill in the professional volunteers and then decrement by 1 point in order to be admitted according to the score.
And some universities have set up different professional grades between different majors.
For example, Jimei University, professional volunteer grade difference is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteer grade is 3 points, there is no difference between other professional volunteers, regarded as parallel volunteers, other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers professional grade difference is 1 point.
When filling out the volunteer application, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school to see if there is a professional grade difference and what is the form of the grade difference. While taking full account of the scores, they should also rationally analyze the proposed school and major. If institutions explicitly adopt the grade difference method for admission in the admissions charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors and improve the chances of admission.
